# Routing Structure

SplitSquad uses Next.js App Router for page routing:

## Main Routes
- `/` - Landing page [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx)
- `/login` - User login [src/app/login/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/login/page.tsx)
- `/signup` - User registration [src/app/signup/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/signup/page.tsx)
- `/dashboard` - User dashboard [src/app/dashboard/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/dashboard/page.tsx)
- `/groups/[id]` - Group details [src/app/groups/[id]/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/groups/[id]/page.tsx)
- `/expenses/[id]` - Expense details [src/app/expenses/[id]/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/expenses/[id]/page.tsx)
- `/payments` - Payments history [src/app/payments/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/payments/page.tsx)

## Navigation
Main application navigation is handled through the AppLayout component [src/components/AppLayout.tsx](mdc:src/components/AppLayout.tsx)
